===Cutting chance===
The chance to successfully cut a red topaz is: <math>\frac{(\text{level}-1)*150/98+91}{256}</math>{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1084600993038389248|date=13 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/HYHsC|archivedate=14 June 2019}}

As such, it is impossible to have a 100% success rate as that would require level 109.
{{Skilling success chart|label=Gem cutting rates
|label1=Opal|low1=128|high1=250|req1=1|color1=gray|image1=Opal.png
|label2=Jade|low2=100|high2=245|req2=13|color2=green|image2=Jade.png
|label3=Red topaz|low3=90|high3=240|req3=16|color3=pink|image3=Red topaz.png
}}

Based on this probability formula, the price of uncut red topaz {{Coins|{{GEP|Uncut red topaz}}}}, and the price of red topaz {{Coins|{{GEP|Red topaz}}}}, the minimum crafting level to breakeven or better when flipping red topaz is {{GemBreakeven
| uncut = {{GEP|Uncut red topaz}}
| cut = {{GEP|Red topaz}}
| r = 1.5306122449
| beta = 91
| gamma = 256}}.

